                <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by rajnew[/i]
[br]Are there any items with clicky buffs/utility that every necro should have?

Of course there are focus effects and such.

Example of what I mean:
--------------------
bard, breath of harmony
- also a ring with instant invis vs. animal (well its all/all, but not much use for it for most people), which breaks charm extremely fast.

clerics have the clicky teleport statue things

I think all melee and hybrid have some kunark era gear that provides some basic utility,
like beastlords have shrink, and a stamina buff, etc.
Stave of shielding, which procs a nice ac/hp/mr buff.

Wizards/druids have a few clicky items that teleport - long casst time and all, still fun to have
--------------

The only things I can think of for a necro are:

circlet of shadows (pre-nerf or nerfed).
- I have a nerfed one and enjoy the right click invis, hasn't really saved my life or anything - but it is very convenient.

black ceramic band
- has a 3.0 sec cast time lifetap(like 6 dmg), hehe.  Its a mana free way to pull.
 I also goof around with it sometimes while waiting for a ldon adv to start :P

edit:
there is a questable all/all illusion mask in POK.  its not difficult to do, but very time consuming

[/quote]</textarea><br /></td>
