                <td bgcolor="#3C4884" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2">Marcus75</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#3C4884" valign="top"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;03/06/2004&nbsp;: 6:51:13 PM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"> I'm level 58. What are these pdots you all seem to obsess over? =:-D~<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"><br />Pdots? If you're referring to peridots, and you're level 58, you'll be finding out soon enough.<br /><br />Stats are rarely truly game-changing. Really only at the extreme ends do stats make a difference in terms of what you can do and how you can do it. Other than that, stats only really affect how quickly or easily you can do the same things you're already doing.<br /><br />Certain focus effects are game-changing. Haste and range focus effects, especially when combined, allow you to handle unsnareable mobs that you COULD NOT do without them.<br />Some spells are game-changing. Touch of Mujaki for instance. Touch of Death is another example. They're spells that don't have a really close lower-level equivalent (well, Deflux:Mujaki, but at the levels you use Deflux it's a different game than the levels you use Mujaki), and they enable tactics you don't have before them.<br /><br />Some useful proc/clicky items:<br />Shai'din Revenant Bauble - clicky Bobbing Corpse (SK DMF equivalent)<br />Orb of Tishan - proc Tashania<br />Willsapper - proc 35% (?) slow<br />Worker Sledgemallet - Proc Overthere port<br />Velious robe (PoG or quested) - click Conjure Corpse<br />Ornate pants - click Rune of Death<br />and of course prenerf CoS and HEB<br /><br />pet focus is also something to aim for, most go for the augment from Takish Hiz (Diamond Prism of Companions)<br /></span></font></td>
              </tr>
